    "#### \n",
    "\n",
    "In this error correction algorithm we use controlled operations extensively. The controlled not gate (CNOT) with control qubit $0$ and target qubit $1$ can be written explicitly as \n",
    "$$ \\mathrm{CNOT}_{0 \\to 1} = \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert \\otimes I + \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert \\otimes X.$$\n",
    "Another way to think of a CNOT gate is a controlled $X$ gate. For any single qubit unitary $U$, we can define a controlled $U$ gate with control qubit $0$ and target qubit $1$ as \n",
    "$$ \\mathrm{CU}_{0 \\to 1} = \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert \\otimes I + \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert \\otimes U.$$\n",
    "We can rewrite the standard CNOT gate using the controlled $Z$ gate by pre and post composing with the Hadamard gate in the target qubit. Recall that $X = HZH$. We can extend this identity to the controlled $X$ and $Z$ gate by\n",
    "\\begin{align*}\n",
    "(I \\otimes H) \\mathrm{CZ}_{0 \\to 1} (I \\otimes H) \n",
    "&= \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert \\otimes I + \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert \\otimes HZH \n",
    "\\\\\n",
    "&= \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert \\otimes I + \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert \\otimes X\n",
    "\\\\\n",
    "&= \\mathrm{CNOT}_{0 \\to 1}.\n",
    "\\end{align*}\n",
    "\n",
    "In general, we cannot switch the control and target qubit in a controlled gate. However, for the controlled $Z$ gate we can. In particular, we have\n",
    "\\begin{align*}\n",
    "\\mathrm{CZ}_{0 \\to 1} \n",
    "&= \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert \\otimes I + \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert \\otimes Z\n",
    "\\\\\n",
    "&=\n",
    "\\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert \\otimes (\\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert + \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert)  + \n",
    "\\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert \\otimes (\\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert - \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert)\n",
    "\\\\\n",
    "&= \n",
    "\\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert \\otimes \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert + \n",
    "\\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert \\otimes \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert +\n",
    "\\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert \\otimes \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert - \n",
    "\\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert \\otimes \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert.\n",
    "\\end{align*}\n",
    "Grouping the terms on the left instead of the right we obtain \n",
    "\\begin{align*}\n",
    "\\mathrm{CZ}_{0 \\to 1}\n",
    "&= \n",
    "(\\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert + \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert) \\otimes \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert + \n",
    "(\\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert - \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert) \\otimes \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert\n",
    "\\\\\n",
    "&=\n",
    "I \\otimes \\lvert 0 \\rangle \\langle 0 \\rvert + Z \\otimes \\lvert 1 \\rangle \\langle 1 \\rvert\n",
    "\\\\\n",
    "&=\n",
    "\\mathrm{CZ}_{1 \\to 0} \n",
    "\\end{align*}\n",
    "\n",
    "Thus, combining these two expressions we obtain\n",
    "$$ \\mathrm{CNOT}_{0 \\to 1} = (I \\otimes H) \\mathrm{CZ}_{0 \\to 1} (I \\otimes H) = (I \\otimes H) \\mathrm{CZ}_{1 \\to 0} (I \\otimes H).$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, we can replace the CNOT gates that control on the data qubits to controlled $Z$ gates that control on the ancilla qubits."
   ]
  },
