    "Thus, we see the bit flip error correction procedure can be implemented as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "0. Encode the logical state in the repeated standard ($Z$) basis.\n",
    "1. For each parity check, prepare an ancilla qubit in the state $\\lvert + \\rangle$ by applying a Hadamard gate to $\\lvert 0 \\rangle$.\n",
    "2. For each ancilla qubit, add controlled $Z$ gates with the ancilla as control and each data qubit appearing in the corresponding parity check as target.\n",
    "3. Apply another Hadamard gate to each ancilla qubit to return them to the standard basis.\n",
    "4. Measure the ancilla qubits to obtain the syndrome.\n",
    "\n",
    "In particular, we use $Z$ operators to extract information about $X$ errors, that is, bit flips."
